S_n = \sum_{k=1}^{n}H_k
H_k
S_n = (n+1)H_n - n
S_n = \sum_{k=1}^{n} H_k = \sum_{k=1}^{n} \sum_{j=1}^{k}\frac{1}{j} 
S_n = \sum_{k=1}^{n}[1+ \frac{1}{2} + \frac{1}{3} + ...+\frac{1}{k-1} + \frac{1}{k}]
S_n=\sum_{j\leqslant k\leqslant n}\frac 1j=\sum_{j=1}^n\sum_{k=j}^n\frac 1j=\sum_{j=1}^n\frac{n-j+1}j=(n+1)H_n-n.
n=1
S_1=H_1=1
(1+1)H_1-1=2-1=1
